      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/2/37",
      "text": [
        " «لاَ بَأْسَ أَنْ يَخْرُجَ بِالسِّلاَحِ مِنْ بَلَدِهِ وَ لَكِنْ إِذَا دَخَلَ مَكَّةَ لَمْ يُظْهِرْهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2331 - Abu Basir asked him (Abu Abdullah (as)) about a man intending to travel to Mecca or Medina and whether it is disliked for him to carry weapons.\nImam (as) replied: \"There is no harm in carrying weapons when leaving his hometown, but when he enters Mecca, he should not display them.\""
        ]
      }
